  %b Description
  %br/
  This method uses
  %b colModel
  names and
  %b url
  parameters from jqGrid
  %br/
  %code
    Calling:
    jQuery("#grid_id").searchGrid( options );
  %br/
  %b options
  %br/
  %b top : 0
  the initial top position of search dialog
  %br/
  %b left: 0
  the initinal left position of search dialog
  %br/
  If the left and top positions are not set the dialog apper on
  %br/
  upper left corner of the grid
  %br/
  = succeed "," do
    %b width: 360
  the width of serch dialog - default 360
  %br/
  = succeed "," do
    %b height: 70
  the height of serch dialog default 70
  %br/
  = succeed "," do
    %b modal: false
  determine if the dialog should be in modal mode default is false
  %br/
  = succeed ",determine" do
    %b drag: true
  if the dialog is dragable default true
  %br/
  = succeed ",the" do
    %b caption: "Search..."
  caption of the dialog
  %br/
  = succeed "," do
    %b Find: "Find"
  the text of the button when you click to search data default Find
  %br/
  = succeed ",the" do
    %b Reset: "Reset"
  text of the button when you click to clear search string default Reset
  %br/
  = succeed "," do
    %b dirty: false
  applicable only in navigator see the last example
  %br/
  These parameters are passed to the url
  %br/
  = succeed "," do
    %b sField:'searchField'
  is the name that is passed to url the value is the name from colModel
  %br/
  = succeed ",is" do
    %b sValue:'searchString'
  the name that is passed to url the value is the entered value
  %br/
  = succeed "," do
    %b sOper: 'searchOper'
  is the name that is passed to the url the value is the type of search - see sopt array
  %br/
  \// translation string for the search options
  %br/
  = succeed "," do
    %b odata : ['equal', 'not equal', 'less', 'less or equal','greater','greater or equal', 'begins with','ends with','contains' ]
  %br/
  \// if you want to change or remove the order change it in sopt
  %br/
  %b sopt: null // ['bw','eq','ne','lt','le','gt','ge','ew','cn']
  %br/
  by default all options are allowed. The codes are as follow:
  %br/
  bw - begins with ( LIKE val% )
  %br/
  eq - equal ( = )
  %br/
  ne - not equal ( <> )
  %br/
  lt - little ( < )
  %br/
  le - little or equal ( <= )
  %br/
  gt - greater ( > )
  %br/
  ge - greater or equal ( >= )
  %br/
  ew - ends with  (LIKE %val )
  %br/
  cn - contain (LIKE %val% )
  %br/
